<subSubSection box="[199,1375,511,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,150,537]" box="[199,1375,511,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[853,987,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">ellipsoideus</emphasis>
referring to the shape of the juxta.
</paragraph>
